  "prompt": "Is there a way to tell if someone in Skype is currently in a call or messaging someone?",
  "response": "Skype does have a few indicators that might give you some insight into someone's activity, but it doesn't offer a direct way to see if someone is in a call or messaging someone else. Here are some clues that might help:\n\n1. **Status Indicators**: Skype users have status indicators that can show if they are \"Online,\" \"Away,\" \"Do Not Disturb,\" or \"Invisible.\" While these don't specifically indicate whether someone is on a call or messaging, they can give you a general idea of their availability.\n\n2. **Call Notification**: If you try to call someone who is already in a call, you might receive a notification saying that the person is currently in another call.\n\n3. **Typing Indicator**: When messaging someone, you may see a typing indicator (three moving dots) if they are currently typing a response, indicating that they are actively engaged in a chat.\n\n4. **Last Seen**: The \"Last Seen\" timestamp can indicate when someone was last active on Skype, though it doesn't indicate specific activities like calls or messaging.\n\nUltimately, Skype prioritizes user privacy, so there are limits to the information you can glean about someone\u2019s activity.",
